<head>SILK PADDING</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">絲填</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SILK USED FOR CAUSING CLOTH to BECOME THICK.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general current word for silk padding that can be used to make warm clothes is mián 綿.</p>
<p>2. Xù 絮 refers to the silk padding put in place.</p>
<p>3. Kuàng 纊 refers to silk padding made of new silk.</p>
<p>4. Yùn 縕 refers to simple padding made of old silk or even of hemp.</p>
        </div>
